Introduction
============

Compilation Notes for Sorcery on Linux

Tested Environment
==================

My Development Environment is:

Ubuntu 26.04 LTS
GCC 14.2+
CMake 3.22+

Git Notes
=========

You'll need git lfs enabled to get the image files in the gfx directory due to 
their size, else you will not get any images.

VSCode Notes
============

VSCode 1.127
C/C++ extension 1.29.3 (note that 1.32.2 currently breaks debugging in VSCode)
CMake Tools extension 1.23.52

I also use bear to produce compile-commands.json for Intelliense plugins

